briefTitle: Study to Assess Efficacy and Safety of PT009 Compared to PT005, PT008, and Symbicort® Turbuhaler® on Lung Function Over 24-Weeks in Subjects With Moderate to Very Severe COPD
officialTitle: A Randomized, Double-Blind, Parallel Group, Multi-Center Study to Assess the Efficacy and Safety of PT009 Compared to PT005, PT008, and Open-label Symbicort® Turbuhaler®, as an Active Control, on Lung Function Over a 24-Week Treatment Period in Subjects With Moderate to Very Severe COPD

interventions.name: BFF MDI 320/9.6 μg
otherNames: Budesonide and Formoterol Fumarate Inhalation Aerosol

interventions.name: BFF MDI 160/9.6 μg
otherNames: Budesonide and Formoterol Fumarate Inhalation Aerosol

summary: This is a Phase III randomized, double-blind, parallel group, multi-center, 24-week lung function study with BFF MDI (320/9.6 μg and 160/9.6 μg) compared to FF MDI 9.6 μg, BD MDI 320 μg, and open-label Symbicort® TBH (200/6 μg) administered BID.

primaryOutcome.measure: Change From Baseline in Morning Pre-dose Trough FEV1 at Week 24 (BFF MDI Versus FF MDI)
